  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal Profile)",
  "description": "This model has been applied in clinical research settings to evaluate hemolysis risk for centrifugal blood pumps under ventricular assist device operating conditions. The CFD-based hemolysis prediction framework uses the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry as a surrogate for Class III VAD devices. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors. Seven factors were formally assessed; six remain flagged as epistemic gaps. All assessed factors show achieved levels at or above required levels under the Minimal profile review, supporting an Accepted decision for limited research use. No structured context-of-use object is provided under the Minimal profile declaration; intended-use scope is conveyed only through this narrative.",
